canvas_summaries.ocr_text: outlolitinio National Union of Women Teachers 41 CROMWELL ROAD, SOUTH KENSINGTON, LONDON, S. W. 7. Salaries and Family Responsibilities 1. Do married men receive higher salaries than bachelors? 2.. Do men with families receive more than those with no children? 3. Do men with large families receive more than those with small families? 4. Do assistant masters, with young children to sup port, receive higher salaries than headmasters whose children have become self- supporting? 5. Do widows with a family to support receive the same salary as men? Since the answer is NO in every case, it is obvious that salaries are not based on responsibilities. Payment is made for services rendered; Women Teachers therefore demand EQUAL PAY FOR WORK OF EQUAL VALUE. Join the N. U. W. T. and help to establish this principle in the teaching profession.
